VALUES ('d2920000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 'Module 5: Locating Simultaneous Conveyances', 'How surveyors and courts locate boundaries created at the same legal instant — the lots of a recorded subdivision plat — where all parcels are of equal dignity, found original monuments control, and any excess or deficiency is apportioned proportionately rather than absorbed by a junior parcel.', 'intermediate', 4, 5, 'published', ARRAY['land-law','boundary-law','texas','nmsu-sur292']::text[], true, 'nmsu-sur292', true, 'approved', 240, 'intermediate')
ON CONFLICT (id) DO UPDATE SET title=EXCLUDED.title, description=EXCLUDED.description, order_index=EXCLUDED.order_index, status='published', is_academic=true, acc_course_id=EXCLUDED.acc_course_id, is_published=true, review_status='approved', tags=EXCLUDED.tags, estimated_hours=EXCLUDED.estimated_hours, updated_at=now();
VALUES ('d2920510-0000-0000-0000-000000000001', 'd2920000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 'What Makes a Conveyance Simultaneous', '', ARRAY['A simultaneous boundary is created in the same legal instant, by the same party, by the same instrument — classically a recorded subdivision plat.','The three requirements: divisions shown on a plat, the map filed and approved, and parcels sold by reference to the approved plat.','All simultaneously created parcels are of equal dignity; no lot is senior, and the order of later sale is immaterial.','Partition decrees and devises by will are treated as subdivisions (equal standing, apportionment).','Excess/deficiency is proportioned by frontage, but ripened unwritten rights still prevail.']::text[], 1, 30, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, ARRAY['land-law','boundary-law','texas','nmsu-sur292']::text[], 'published', true, 'approved', true, NULL, ARRAY['Define a simultaneously created boundary and list the three requirements that establish one.','Explain why simultaneously created parcels are of equal dignity and have no senior rights among themselves.','Recognize other transactions (partition decrees, devises by will) that are treated as simultaneous conveyances.']::text[]);
VALUES ('d2920510-0000-0000-0000-000000000002', 'd2920000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 'What Controls a Subdivision Boundary: The Order of Evidence', '', ARRAY['Protracted lots are located by measurement from the subdivision boundary; surveyed-and-monumented lots are located by the original monuments.','Original lines established by the creating surveyor are unalterable except by resubdivision; an erroneous later line must be put back where the original was.','Found original monuments control over the plat; where map and ground disagree, the map yields to the ground.','Order of control: found monuments > natural monuments > artificial monuments/lines run > conforming improvements > plat record > scaled width.','The exterior boundary still yields to the senior rights of adjoining tracts.']::text[], 2, 35, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, ARRAY['land-law','boundary-law','texas','nmsu-sur292']::text[], 'published', true, 'approved', true, NULL, ARRAY['State the order of controlling evidence for locating subdivision lot lines.','Distinguish lots created by protraction from lots created by survey and monumentation.','Explain why found original monuments control over the plat record, and how senior rights still bind the exterior boundary.']::text[]);
VALUES ('d2920510-0000-0000-0000-000000000003', 'd2920000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 'Single Proportionate Measurement: Apportioning a Block', '', ARRAY['Proportion only as a last resort, after found monuments and all better evidence are exhausted.','Single proportion factor k = measured total / record total; corrected lot = k times record lot.','For equal lots, corrected frontage = measured total / number of lots.','Find an interior corner with cumulative proportion: measured total times (cumulative record distance / record total).','Never distribute excess/deficiency across an undisturbed original interior monument — proportion each segment separately.']::text[], 3, 40, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, ARRAY['land-law','boundary-law','texas','nmsu-sur292']::text[], 'published', true, 'approved', true, NULL, ARRAY['Explain when proportioning applies and why it is a last resort.','Compute the corrected frontage of each lot by single proportionate measurement.','Compute the corrected distance to an interior lot corner using cumulative proportion.']::text[]);
VALUES ('d2920510-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 'd2920000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 'Excess, Deficiency, Remnants, and Double Proportion', '', ARRAY['Total Δ = measured total − record total; per-lot adjustment is Δ times the lot''s share of the record total (Δ/n for equal lots).','An isolable blunder is placed in the lot where it occurs; error in one block is never prorated into another, and street width is normally not prorated.','If the end lot''s dimension is omitted it absorbs the excess/deficiency; the remnant rule throws surplus onto an irregular end lot but is disfavored.','A single lost corner between two found corners is restored by m × a/(a+b) along the line.','Double proportionate measurement (two-direction restoration) is a BLM/PLSS method; in Texas it is a fallback with no controlling case.']::text[], 4, 35, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, ARRAY['land-law','boundary-law','texas','nmsu-sur292']::text[], 'published', true, 'approved', true, NULL, ARRAY['Compute the total excess/deficiency in a block and the per-lot adjustment.','Identify when a blunder is placed where it occurs versus prorated, and explain the remnant rule and its dangers.','Describe single-proportion restoration of a lost corner between two found corners, and the concept of double proportionate measurement.']::text[]);
VALUES ('d2920510-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 'd2920000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 'Rules of Construction for Combined Descriptions', '', ARRAY['A portion ''of'' a subdivision lot is measured from the street side line; a portion ''of'' a metes-and-bounds tract from the boundary line — even in a street.','An ''of'' lineal measurement is presumed at right angles to the boundary unless specified.','A ''west half'' is presumed by area; divide parallel-sided lots on the mean bearing, non-parallel lots north–south.','Laid-off areas default to a parallelogram (side), a square (on a line), or near-equal-sided parallelogram (corner).','All such canons are gap-fillers, subordinate in Texas to expressed intent, footsteps, and the dignity of calls.']::text[], 5, 30, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, ARRAY['land-law','boundary-law','texas','nmsu-sur292']::text[], 'published', true, 'approved', true, NULL, ARRAY['Apply the construction rules for ''part-of-a-lot'' (an ''of'') descriptions in subdivisions and metes-and-bounds tracts.','Apply the construction rules for fractional (''half'') conveyances and for dividing lots into halves.','State good-practice rules for writing combined descriptions.']::text[]);
  'd2920550-0000-0000-0000-000000000001', 'Single proportionate distribution — corrected lot frontage', 'Single proportionate distribution — corrected lot frontage', 'Boundary Law — Simultaneous Conveyances', 'Apportionment', 'numeric_input', 'medium', 'A block of {{n}} equal lots was platted, each with a record frontage of {{rec:f2}} ft (record total {{recTotal:f2}} ft). A resurvey finds the actual measured distance between the two original found block-corner monuments is {{meas:f2}} ft. Using single proportionate measurement, what is the corrected frontage (ft) of each lot?', 'meas/n', '{"decimals":2,"unit":"ft","tolerance":0.02}', '[{"name":"n","type":"integer","min":4,"max":10},{"name":"rec","type":"float","min":45,"max":120,"decimals":2},{"name":"surplus","type":"float","min":-4,"max":4,"decimals":2}]'::jsonb, '[{"name":"recTotal","formula":"n*rec"},{"name":"meas","formula":"recTotal+surplus"}]'::jsonb, '[{"step_number":1,"title":"Record total","formula":"n × record","calculation_template":"{{n}} × {{rec:f2}} = {{recTotal:f2}} ft"},{"step_number":2,"title":"Proportion factor k","calculation_template":"k = {{meas:f2}} ÷ {{recTotal:f2}}"},{"step_number":3,"title":"Corrected lot frontage","result_template":"{{meas:f2}} ÷ {{n}} = {{_answer}} ft"}]'::jsonb, '{"method":"none"}'::jsonb, 'Single proportionate measurement distributes the {{surplus:f2}} ft excess/deficiency in proportion to record frontage. For equal lots the corrected frontage is the measured total divided by the number of lots: {{meas:f2}} ÷ {{n}} = {{_answer}} ft.', 'd2920000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', ARRAY['land-law','boundary-law','texas','nmsu-sur292','practice']::text[], true, 'seed:nmsu-sur292');
  'd2920550-0000-0000-0000-000000000002', 'Cumulative proportion — distance to an interior lot corner', 'Cumulative proportion — distance to an interior lot corner', 'Boundary Law — Simultaneous Conveyances', 'Apportionment', 'numeric_input', 'medium', 'A block has {{n}} equal record lots of {{rec:f2}} ft each (record total {{recTotal:f2}} ft) between two found original end monuments measured at {{meas:f2}} ft. By single proportionate measurement, what is the corrected distance (ft) from the first found monument to the corner between lot {{i}} and lot {{i}}+1?', 'meas*(cumRec/recTotal)', '{"decimals":2,"unit":"ft","tolerance":0.03}', '[{"name":"n","type":"integer","min":5,"max":10},{"name":"rec","type":"float","min":45,"max":110,"decimals":2},{"name":"surplus","type":"float","min":-4,"max":4,"decimals":2},{"name":"i","type":"integer","min":1,"max":4}]'::jsonb, '[{"name":"recTotal","formula":"n*rec"},{"name":"meas","formula":"recTotal+surplus"},{"name":"cumRec","formula":"i*rec"}]'::jsonb, '[{"step_number":1,"title":"Cumulative record distance","formula":"i × record","calculation_template":"{{i}} × {{rec:f2}} = {{cumRec:f2}} ft"},{"step_number":2,"title":"Apply proportion","formula":"measured × (cumulative record ÷ record total)","calculation_template":"{{meas:f2}} × ({{cumRec:f2}} ÷ {{recTotal:f2}})"},{"step_number":3,"title":"Corrected distance","result_template":"= {{_answer}} ft"}]'::jsonb, '{"method":"none"}'::jsonb, 'Use cumulative proportion to avoid accumulating per-lot rounding: corrected distance = measured total × (cumulative record distance ÷ record total) = {{meas:f2}} × ({{cumRec:f2}} ÷ {{recTotal:f2}}) = {{_answer}} ft.', 'd2920000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', ARRAY['land-law','boundary-law','texas','nmsu-sur292','practice']::text[], true, 'seed:nmsu-sur292');
  'd2920550-0000-0000-0000-000000000003', 'Excess/deficiency — total surplus and per-lot adjustment', 'Excess/deficiency — total surplus and per-lot adjustment', 'Boundary Law — Simultaneous Conveyances', 'Apportionment', 'numeric_input', 'easy', 'A block of {{n}} equal record lots of {{rec:f2}} ft each (record total {{recTotal:f2}} ft) is measured at {{meas:f2}} ft between found original monuments. What is the per-lot adjustment (ft) that must be added to (or subtracted from) each record frontage?', 'delta/n', '{"decimals":3,"unit":"ft","tolerance":0.005}', '[{"name":"n","type":"integer","min":4,"max":12},{"name":"rec","type":"float","min":40,"max":100,"decimals":2},{"name":"delta","type":"float","min":-5,"max":5,"decimals":2}]'::jsonb, '[{"name":"recTotal","formula":"n*rec"},{"name":"meas","formula":"recTotal+delta"}]'::jsonb, '[{"step_number":1,"title":"Total excess/deficiency","formula":"measured − record total","calculation_template":"{{meas:f2}} − {{recTotal:f2}} = {{delta:f2}} ft"},{"step_number":2,"title":"Per-lot adjustment","formula":"total ÷ n","result_template":"{{delta:f2}} ÷ {{n}} = {{_answer}} ft"}]'::jsonb, '{"method":"none"}'::jsonb, 'Total excess/deficiency Δ = {{meas:f2}} − {{recTotal:f2}} = {{delta:f2}} ft. For equal lots the per-lot adjustment is Δ ÷ n = {{delta:f2}} ÷ {{n}} = {{_answer}} ft (positive = add to each lot, negative = subtract).', 'd2920000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', ARRAY['land-law','boundary-law','texas','nmsu-sur292','practice']::text[], true, 'seed:nmsu-sur292');
  'd2920550-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 'Single-proportion restoration of a lost corner between two found corners', 'Single-proportion restoration of a lost corner between two found corners', 'Boundary Law — Simultaneous Conveyances', 'Proportionate measurement', 'numeric_input', 'medium', 'A lost corner lies on a straight line between two found original corners. Its record distances to the two found monuments are {{a:f2}} ft and {{b:f2}} ft (record span {{recSpan:f2}} ft). The measured span between the found monuments is {{m:f2}} ft. By single proportionate measurement, what is the corrected distance (ft) from the first found monument to the lost corner?', 'm*(a/(a+b))', '{"decimals":2,"unit":"ft","tolerance":0.03}', '[{"name":"a","type":"float","min":150,"max":450,"decimals":2},{"name":"b","type":"float","min":120,"max":400,"decimals":2},{"name":"spanDelta","type":"float","min":-5,"max":6,"decimals":2}]'::jsonb, '[{"name":"recSpan","formula":"a+b"},{"name":"m","formula":"a+b+spanDelta"}]'::jsonb, '[{"step_number":1,"title":"Record span","formula":"a + b","calculation_template":"{{a:f2}} + {{b:f2}} = {{recSpan:f2}} ft"},{"step_number":2,"title":"Proportion","formula":"measured × a ÷ (a + b)","calculation_template":"{{m:f2}} × {{a:f2}} ÷ {{recSpan:f2}}"},{"step_number":3,"title":"Lost-corner distance","result_template":"= {{_answer}} ft from the first found monument"}]'::jsonb, '{"method":"none"}'::jsonb, 'Single-proportion restoration: X = m × a/(a+b) = {{m:f2}} × {{a:f2}} ÷ {{recSpan:f2}} = {{_answer}} ft. The {{spanDelta:f2}} ft surplus/shortage in the span is split in proportion to the record distances a and b.', 'd2920000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', ARRAY['land-law','boundary-law','texas','nmsu-sur292','practice']::text[], true, 'seed:nmsu-sur292');

-- ===== Module 6: Module 6: Water Rights & Water Boundaries =====
